details.description: Discover Higher Grounds Café by Manolo's! We're more than just a coffee shop; we're a community hub serving exceptional non-profit Colombian coffee. Indulge in delectable pastries and artisan gelato, perfect for a sweet treat. If you're on the go, grab one of our delicious and convenient food options. Come experience the warmth and community spirit that makes Higher Grounds a unique destination.

posts.body:
✨ New Grab & Go Sandwiches at Higher Grounds Café by Manolo's! ✨ Freshly made, packed with flavor, and ready when you are.
🥩 Jubilee Chimichurri – Tender roast beef with pickled onions & vibrant chimichurri sauce. 🥪 Corinthiam Club – Turkey & crispy bacon with giardiniera aioli and crunchy pickles. 🇮🇹 Verità Italiana – Ham, salami, pesto & balsamic in a bold Italian classic. 🍫 Sweet Salvation – Chocolate bread filled with Nutella, peanut butter & fresh fruit.

reviews_data.review_text: What a great gem that just happens to be found in a church. Arguably the best coffee in town. Delicious treats. An atmosphere that's a blend of comfortable, family, social, meet up,  and stress free. Everyone is just nice without feeling forced or rushed. Amazing artwork too. It doesn't try to be more than it is which is refreshing and fantastic. Grab a coffee and a pastry (or maybe some ice cream) and you'll thank me. I highly recommend checking out Higher Grounds.

Coffee is good. In and out. Spaces to sit. Places to walk. Highly recommended for anyone needing some good coffee. Plus this church is spectacular! The vibes here are top notch. Im sure if you’re here for coffee, you’re already here for the Lord!

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace, Counter seating

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks!!! We're truly delighted by your visit and that it was such a positive experience. You're always welcome in our sanctuary.

reviews_data.review_text: Modern coffee shop inside the complex of the Methodist Church of Myers Park. It’s hidden, more people should know about it.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your visit — we’ll see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: I had the BEST ever experience here! The food was beyond amazing and the atmosphere was exactly what I needed. There are tons of different styles of chairs and tables, to accommodate people who need a quiet place to work or friends who need a relaxing spot to catch-up. My coffee was delicious (iced caramel mocha) and my friend ordered a chai tea. They literally brought the infuser right to the table and showed her how to use it. She poured in her own cream and they gave her a sifter for the cocoa powder. So cool! They also have tons of treats, including gelato. More than anything, though, the service and restaurant itself are exceptional! I spoke to Manolo himself - who made himself beyond available - for about 10 minutes and he was so welcoming. I loved hearing about the opening of this cafe and other aspects of his life. Even better, 100% of the profits are donated. I have quite literally never been somewhere so amazing!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're truly grateful for your kind words and so happy to know your experience was such a positive one. Every detail is prepared with love and care, and it means a lot to know it was appreciated. You're always welcome back anytime!

reviews_data.review_text: Great to grab a cafecito or cafe con leche, take a meeting and enjoy the views.
I absolutely love this place

I’ve been to Higher Grounds a few times to catch up over coffee with friends and it’s becoming my go to place.  The coffee, atmosphere, and seating are all great…but my new favorite thing is the key lime tart.  I can’t wait to go back and get another.  Parking availability varies; you may need to park in the Myers Park UMC lot across the street.

Manolo is committed to hiring highly-qualified and diverse staff, they use high-quality coffee from Colombia, and their profits go toward mission work.  ❤️
The perfect meet up location for our monthly veterans’ coffee. The staff has been accommodating to our 12-18 person group that arrives at opening time. Thanks to the staff for making us all welcome.

Best kept secret of Myers Park! Here’s how to zip in for fast lovely service, coffee on par with Not Just Coffee...
Enter MP Methodist lot on right side of Queens Rd, just past Oxford. Swing counter clockwise in the parking lot and follow signs to entrance. There are a few "To Go Only" spaces right at the door. Fresh, welcoming atmosphere. You can exit RIGHT onto Providence RD OR back on Queens Rd.

Very uncomfortable experience. No outlets at most seats, baristas are kind but do not know how to make the drinks on their menu. I ordered a flat white and received brewed coffee with a splash of milk. There is no music playing so speaking is very uncomfortable because it’s insanely quiet. My husband ordered an americano and they asked “medium or large” and he asked “does the large have one more shot?” And they replied “they both come with two shots” so essentially you’re paying $1.50 extra for water.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you for taking the time to share your experience. I'm truly sorry we didn't meet your expectations during your visit.

I apologize for the inconvenience regarding the outlets; while the seats along the walls do have access to outlets, we understand that not having them available at every seat can be frustrating. We’re also in the process of installing speakers, so music will be playing soon to create a more comfortable atmosphere.

Regarding your drinks, I’m sorry to hear that the Flat White and Americano did not meet your expectations. It seems there may have been some confusion during the preparation, and we will address this with our team to ensure it doesn't happen again.

I’d love to discuss your experience further to make it right. Please reach out to me directly at byett@mpumc.org, and I’ll personally ensure your concerns are addressed.

Thank you again for your feedback—it helps us improve and serve our customers better.

reviews_data.review_text: What a gorgeous place!!!! The atmosphere is amazing, comfy, and food is delicious as it has always been with Manolo.

My wife and I visited Higher Grounds recently and loved it here. The coffee shop is brand new and is very spacious with plenty of seating all around. This is a great place for anybody that needs some time away and wants some peace and quiet. It definitely had a nice calm vibe to it when we were there.

They offer a good variety from coffee, pastries and gelato here. The coffee was very good! We’ll have to try the pastries and gelato on the next visit.

The coffee shop is a little confusing to find if it’s your first time visiting. If you’re driving you’ll have to enter from Queens Road and you enter where the church is. You cannot enter from Providence Road as that is a one way road to exit out the parking lot. There will be a sign at the entrance of the parking lot that states the coffee shop is there. Once you get into the parking lot you’ll see some dedicated spots for the coffee shop so you know you’re at the right spot. Just walk a few steps down the alley of the parking lot and you’ll see the coffee shop sign and enter thru the double doors. It’s really easy once you find it. We were thankful parking was very easy and convenient.

Overall, we enjoyed Higher Grounds and will return back! This is a great coffee shop to the Queens/Myers Park area.
This is a great place to grab coffee/treat to meet up with a friend or to work in a calm and beautiful atmosphere. The service was fast and friendly and I loved the seating options.
